The model reports three classical global tests, all of which assess whether the covariates
jointly improve the fit: the likelihood-ratio test, the Wald test, and the score test. They
usually agree closely, and the likelihood-ratio test is generally preferred.

::: {#15db4e72 .cell execution_count=10}
``` {.python .cell-code}
# Compare the three classical global tests (they should be similar)
print("likelihood ratio:", round(cox.lr_stat_, 3))
print("Wald:", round(cox.wald_stat_, 3))
print("score:", round(cox.score_stat_, 3))
```

